=head1 DESCRIPTION

A type of analysis rule that enables the table owner to approve custom
SQL queries on their configured tables. It supports differential
privacy.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AdditionalAnalyses => Str

An indicator as to whether additional analyses (such as Clean Rooms ML)
can be applied to the output of the direct query.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AllowedAnalyses => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The ARN of the analysis templates that are allowed by the custom
analysis rule.


=head2 AllowedAnalysisProviders => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The IDs of the Amazon Web Services accounts that are allowed to query
by the custom analysis rule. Required when C<allowedAnalyses> is
C<ANY_QUERY>.


=head2 DifferentialPrivacy => L<Paws::CleanRooms::DifferentialPrivacyConfiguration>

The differential privacy configuration.


=head2 DisallowedOutputColumns => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

A list of columns that aren't allowed to be shown in the query output.



